{
  "stem": "9701.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And she's saying that she's traveling to the east and she's saying a very final goodbye to me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But until many, many years later, I really chose that postcard to say or interpreted that postcard to say something very different, that she was traveling in an easterly direction.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I thought well, Kippenheim, the village where we lived is in an easterly direction and maybe she's going back home.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Maybe that's a good idea.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And where she's saying a very final goodbye, I thought it was the kind of goodbye you say when you go on a trip and, you know, hope to see you again soon.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, you know, both my parents had said it may be a very long time before you hear from us again.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And how long is a long time?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Is it a week, a month, a year?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I just kept on telling myself a long time just isn't over yet.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think in many ways, it was probably a survival mechanism on my part, because I don't think I could have accepted the fact that my parents are no longer alive.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then in-- and so I just kept on waiting, you know, until the long time will finally be over, because I fervently hoped and wished that I would be reunited with them again somewhere, somehow.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And then in 1956, I received two letters from a French organization, telling me that both my parents had been deported to the concentration camp Auschwitz, A-U-S-C-H-W-I-T-Z, on September 11th, 1942.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And by 1956 when these letters arrived, I certainly knew a lot more about what Auschwitz was about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I knew also that there were a handful of people who survived.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
